the gay and lesbian
community when

00:03:04.790 --> 00:03:07.160
I worked as a professional
actor and singer.

00:03:07.160 --> 00:03:09.740
It chronicles my journey
to becoming a pastor

00:03:09.740 --> 00:03:12.380
and going to seminary,
and then this viral blog

00:03:12.380 --> 00:03:14.000
post that happened in 2010.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:16.430
And so it kind of
shares my own education

00:03:16.430 --> 00:03:19.310
about the gay community
and the gay rights movement

00:03:19.310 --> 00:03:20.900
and gay history.

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:24.200
And then it's also, secondly,
it's part theological.

00:03:24.200 --> 00:03:27.920
And so I look at the six
main passages in the Bible

00:03:27.920 --> 00:03:30.500
that are often used to
talk about homosexuality.

00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:33.290
And I do that looking from
both a traditional viewpoint

00:03:33.290 --> 00:03:37.000
and a progressive viewpoint.

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:39.230
And so looking at the
Greek and the Hebrew.

00:03:39.230 --> 00:03:41.480
And how do scholars
or Christians

00:03:41.480 --> 00:03:45.080
or church communities come
to a certain conclusion

00:03:45.080 --> 00:03:49.070
about sexuality from a
traditional viewpoint, but also

00:03:49.070 --> 00:03:52.320
a more progressive viewpoint,
and kind of that spectrum.

00:03:52.320 --> 00:03:54.890
And then I also talk
about what is the church,

00:03:54.890 --> 00:03:58.070
and how can the church community
or spiritual communities

00:03:58.070 --> 00:04:01.910
remain together, even if they
might differ on certain things.

00:04:01.910 --> 00:04:05.180
And how can we, instead
of fighting ugly, how can

00:04:05.180 --> 00:04:08.880
we really learn and
understand from one another.

00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:10.700
And then finally,
it's part pastoral.

00:04:10.700 --> 00:04:14.060
