00:36:23.810 --> 00:36:26.300
been negative repercussions
or feedback like that you've

00:36:26.300 --> 00:36:28.460
gotten from within the
religious community,

00:36:28.460 --> 00:36:30.920
from within LGBTQ community.

00:36:30.920 --> 00:36:32.420
I mean, how has that been?

00:36:32.420 --> 00:36:35.050
NATHAN ALBERT: Yeah.

00:36:35.050 --> 00:36:38.080
So one of the things
I do in the book

00:36:38.080 --> 00:36:40.480
that I think confuses
people, is especially

00:36:40.480 --> 00:36:43.600
in the section on
the Bible, I lay out

00:36:43.600 --> 00:36:45.280
a whole spectrum of belief.

00:36:45.280 --> 00:36:48.100
And what I don't do is
say you need to believe

00:36:48.100 --> 00:36:49.300
one side or the other.

00:36:49.300 --> 00:36:50.620
And I'm intentional in that.

00:36:50.620 --> 00:36:53.650
Because every book I've read
says, hey, if you believe this,

00:36:53.650 --> 00:36:55.630
you're a bigot and a homophobe.

00:36:55.630 --> 00:36:56.920
You need to believe this.

00:36:56.920 --> 00:36:58.360
And then other
books say if you're

00:36:58.360 --> 00:37:01.150
like progressive and
really open and affirming,

00:37:01.150 --> 00:37:04.870
you're like this crazy liberal,
and you need to believe this.

00:37:04.870 --> 00:37:06.710
And I don't think any
of that is helpful.

00:37:06.710 --> 00:37:08.251
So what I did is I
laid it out there.

00:37:08.251 --> 00:37:10.640
And then I was like, you got
to figure it out yourself.

00:37:10.640 --> 00:37:11.140
Good luck.

00:37:11.140 --> 00:37:12.070
You're all adults.

00:37:12.070 --> 00:37:16.060
Like you should be able to
like figure out what you think.

00:37:16.060 --> 00:37:18.520
But that actually bothers
a lot of people, right.

00:37:18.520 --> 00:37:23.710
Because some are saying well,
because you didn't say this,

00:37:23.710 --> 00:37:26.050
it means you must believe this.

00:37:26.050 --> 00:37:28.060
Which means you're like that.

00:37:28.060 --> 00:37:31.340
And I'm like oh, no, that
didn't-- no, not true at all.

00:37:31.340 --> 00:37:32.440
Or vice versa.

00:37:32.440 --> 00:37:37.030
Whether it's like when we
did the pride parade, right,

00:37:37.030 --> 00:37:38.940
like some people
said, well, they're

00:37:38.940 --> 00:37:40.820
wolves in sheep's
clothing, right.

00:37:40.820 --> 00:37:43.230
So you're Christians,
but you still

00:37:43.230 --> 00:37:45.840
believe this about sexuality.

00:37:45.840 --> 00:37:48.152
So really you're out to get us.

00:37:48.152 --> 00:37:49.110
And you're tricking us.

00:37:49.110 --> 00:37:52.500
So I think that's happened.

00:37:52.500 --> 00:37:57.090
And yeah, other
people, repercussions.

00:37:57.090 --> 00:38:00.010
There have been quite a few.

00:38:00.010 --> 00:38:02.500
But I guess it comes
with the terrain.

00:38:02.500 --> 00:38:06.770
I guess it's a heated, yeah,
it's heated for people.

00:38:06.770 --> 00:38:09.550
And I think some
people, when they're

00:38:09.550 --> 00:38:14.530
challenged in a new way of
thinking, rather than seeing it

00:38:14.530 --> 00:38:18.080
as an opportunity for
growth, it becomes a threat.

00:38:18.080 --> 00:38:20.040
And so for me in this
process, this isn't--

00:38:20.040 --> 00:38:21.790
I've never been
threatened in any of this.

00:38:21.790 --> 00:38:22.870
I think this is exciting.

00:38:22.870 --> 00:38:24.220
Like I'm learning something new.

00:38:24.220 --> 00:38:27.250
Or I never knew those
Greek words in the Bible

00:38:27.250 --> 00:38:28.690
could be translated this way.

00:38:28.690 --> 00:38:30.644
In the English it
always says this.

00:38:30.644 --> 00:38:32.060
Oh, maybe it means
something else.

00:38:32.060 --> 00:38:35.350
Like that's an exciting process
for me of growth and learning.

00:38:35.350 --> 00:38:40.514
Rather than a oh, I'm afraid of
what that might mean, you know.

00:38:40.514 --> 00:38:41.680
PHILLIP KNOLL: Right, right.

00:38:41.680 --> 00:38:42.885
Yeah, absolutely.

00:38:42.885 --> 00:38:45.010
