way to live.

00:40:13.870 --> 00:40:18.310
And so for me, there
are other religions

00:40:18.310 --> 00:40:22.830
that I think there are
beautiful ways to live.

00:40:22.830 --> 00:40:28.300
And I love the way of Jesus
and following that way.

00:40:28.300 --> 00:40:29.870
Yes, so you're right.

00:40:29.870 --> 00:40:32.452
Like I do think there are--

00:40:32.452 --> 00:40:34.910
I just think Christians have
got to get their act together.

00:40:34.910 --> 00:40:39.570
You know, like when an atheist
lives a better Christian life,

00:40:39.570 --> 00:40:43.280
whatever that might mean,
than Christians, well,

00:40:43.280 --> 00:40:47.240
it just makes you question what
is the definition of Christian

00:40:47.240 --> 00:40:47.870
then.

00:40:47.870 --> 00:40:49.245
AUDIENCE: Right,
or why religion.

00:40:49.245 --> 00:40:51.170
NATHAN ALBERT: Or why, yeah.

00:40:51.170 --> 00:40:54.400
But I think the pursuit of--

00:40:54.400 --> 00:40:56.800
yeah, the pursuit
of spiritual things

00:40:56.800 --> 00:41:03.830
is like searching for
treasure, I guess.

00:41:03.830 --> 00:41:07.660
And I'm not sure that
answers your question.

00:41:07.660 --> 00:41:09.057
But yeah, I doubt.

00:41:09.057 --> 00:41:10.140
And I think that's a part.

00:41:10.140 --> 00:41:17.500
I think doubt is a part of
